OL,6,FMads was required to wear a helmet
OL,7,Fwhen standing or walking for more than
OL,8,Fa year to protect his skull. He was
OL,9,Fforced to give up karate, biking and
OL,10,Fgolf during that time.
OL,12,FHe underwent further surgery to repair
OL,13,Fdamage to his skull, including fitting
OL,14,Fa titanium plate, in January this year.
OL,16,FMads still suffers from memory, speech
OL,17,Fand language issues and his brain
OL,18,Ffunction is still impaired.
